# MARS Credential Script Configuration
#
# This file configures custom credential script paths for MARS.
#
# SETUP (Option 1 - Auto-sourced by Plugin):
#   1. Copy this file: cp .credential-scripts.example .credential-scripts
#   2. Edit .credential-scripts and uncomment desired credentials
#   3. Update paths to point to your actual credential scripts
#   4. Source mars-env.config - it will auto-source this file!
#
# SETUP (Option 2 - Shell Profile):
#   1. Copy relevant exports to ~/.bashrc or ~/.zshrc
#   2. Update paths to point to your actual credential scripts
#   3. Source mars-env.config to activate
#
# Auto-Sourcing:
#   mars-env.config automatically sources hooks/.credential-scripts from
#   all registered MARS plugins. No need to manually add to shell profile
#   if using the plugin-based approach (Option 1).
#
# PRIORITY ORDER:
#   1. Already set (environment variable)
#   2. Custom script path (${VARNAME}_SCRIPT - this file)
#   3. Conventional script (CREDENTIAL_SCRIPT_DIR/conventional-name.sh)
#   4. File-based (.env-credentials file)
#   5. Default value (placeholder)
#
# DOCUMENTATION:
#   - Complete Guide: core/docs/CREDENTIAL_MANAGEMENT.md
#   - Example Scripts: mars-dev/scripts/credential-scripts/examples/
#   - Test Suite: core/tests/test_credential_loading.py

###############################################################################
# Method A: Custom Script Paths (Recommended for Existing Scripts)
###############################################################################
#
# Use this method when you already have credential scripts for other tools
# (e.g., AskSage, GitLab CLI, etc.) and want to reuse them with MARS.
#
# Benefits:
# - No duplication of scripts
# - Share scripts between MARS and other processes
# - Use your existing script names (no renaming required)

# Zotero API Key
# Used by: Zotero MCP server, literature sync
# Get from: https://www.zotero.org/settings/keys
# Shared with: AskSage (if you use Zotero for research)
#
# export ZOTERO_API_KEY_SCRIPT="$HOME/.credentials/asksage-token.sh"
# export ZOTERO_API_KEY_SCRIPT="$HOME/.credentials/zotero.sh"

# GitLab Personal Access Token
# Used by: GitLab MCP tools, GitLab API access
# Get from: http://localhost:9080/-/profile/personal_access_tokens
# Scopes required: api, read_repository, write_repository
#
# export GITLAB_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN_SCRIPT="$HOME/.credentials/gitlab.sh"
# export GITLAB_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN_SCRIPT="$HOME/.credentials/gitlab-token.sh"

# VNC Password
# Used by: Remote desktop access to E6 development container
# Security: Should be strong random password (16+ characters)
#
# export VNC_PASSWORD_SCRIPT="$HOME/.credentials/vnc.sh"
# export VNC_PASSWORD_SCRIPT="$HOME/.credentials/vnc-password.sh"

# PostgreSQL Database Password
# Used by: PostgreSQL database service (context-persistence)
# Security: Auto-generated strong password recommended
#
# export POSTGRES_PASSWORD_SCRIPT="$HOME/.credentials/postgres.sh"
# export POSTGRES_PASSWORD_SCRIPT="$HOME/.credentials/postgres-password.sh"

# Neo4j Graph Database Password
# Used by: Neo4j knowledge graph service
# Security: Auto-generated strong password recommended
#
# export NEO4J_PASSWORD_SCRIPT="$HOME/.credentials/neo4j.sh"
# export NEO4J_PASSWORD_SCRIPT="$HOME/.credentials/neo4j-password.sh"

# Milvus MinIO Secret Key
# Used by: Milvus vector database object storage
# Security: Auto-generated strong password recommended
#
# export MILVUS_MINIO_SECRET_KEY_SCRIPT="$HOME/.credentials/milvus.sh"
# export MILVUS_MINIO_SECRET_KEY_SCRIPT="$HOME/.credentials/milvus-minio.sh"

###############################################################################
# Method B: Conventional Directory (Recommended for MARS-Only Scripts)
###############################################################################
#
# Use this method when creating new scripts specifically for MARS.
# All scripts must be in CREDENTIAL_SCRIPT_DIR and follow naming convention:
#   - zotero-api-key.sh
#   - gitlab-personal-access-token.sh
#   - vnc-password.sh
#   - postgres-password.sh
#   - neo4j-password.sh
#   - milvus-minio-secret-key.sh
#
# Benefits:
# - Simple setup (one environment variable)
# - All credential scripts in one organized location
# - Conventional names are self-documenting
#
# export CREDENTIAL_SCRIPT_DIR="$HOME/.mars/credential-scripts"
# export CREDENTIAL_SCRIPT_DIR="$HOME/.config/mars/credentials"

###############################################################################
# Method C: Hybrid Approach (Best Flexibility)
###############################################################################
#
# Combine both methods! Custom paths take priority over conventional directory.
#
# Example: Share Zotero script with AskSage, use conventional for others
#
# export ZOTERO_API_KEY_SCRIPT="$HOME/.credentials/asksage-token.sh"
# export CREDENTIAL_SCRIPT_DIR="$HOME/.mars/credential-scripts"
# # Conventional directory contains: gitlab-personal-access-token.sh, etc.

###############################################################################
# Password Manager Integration Examples
###############################################################################
#
# Your credential scripts can fetch from password managers, Vault, etc.
# Each script must:
#   - Be executable (chmod +x)
#   - Output credential to stdout (single line)
#   - Exit with code 0 on success
#
# 1Password CLI:
#   #!/bin/bash
#   op item get "Zotero API Key" --fields password 2>/dev/null
#
# Bitwarden CLI:
#   #!/bin/bash
#   bw get password "Zotero API Key" 2>/dev/null
#
# pass (Unix Password Manager):
#   #!/bin/bash
#   pass show mars/zotero-api-key 2>/dev/null
#
# HashiCorp Vault:
#   #!/bin/bash
#   vault kv get -field=api-key secret/mars/zotero 2>/dev/null
#
# AWS Secrets Manager:
#   #!/bin/bash
#   aws secretsmanager get-secret-value \
#       --secret-id mars/zotero-api-key \
#       --query SecretString \
#       --output text 2>/dev/null

###############################################################################
# Quick Setup Instructions
###############################################################################
#
# 1. Choose your method (A, B, or C above)
#
# 2. Copy relevant exports to your shell profile:
#    vim ~/.bashrc  # or ~/.zshrc
#
# 3. Add your credential script paths (uncomment and edit above)
#
# 4. Create/verify your credential scripts are executable:
#    chmod +x $HOME/.credentials/*.sh
#
# 5. Test your setup:
#    source mars-env.config
#    echo $ZOTERO_API_KEY  # Should show your key, not "NOT_CONFIGURED"
#
# 6. Validate everything works:
#    mars-dev doctor  # Should show "âœ“ All credential security checks passed"
